Position Title: Project Cost Control Analyst

Team and Location: Parkland Refining (B.C.) LTD. – Burnaby, BC


Company Profile:
Parkland is unique. We fuel communities by safely delivering high-quality petroleum products to motorists, businesses, consumers and wholesale customers across North America. Through unrivaled dependability and service, we connect communities to the products they need to heat their homes, fuel their industries and drive their economies.

Parkland is strong. We are one of North America’s fastest growing and largest independent distributors and marketers of fuels and lubricants. Our family includes Bluewave Energy, Columbia Fuels, Elbow River Marketing, Island Petroleum, Fas Gas Plus, Farstad Oil, Les Pétroles Parkland, Pioneer Energy, Sparlings, Superpumper Inc., Ultramar, and most recently Parkland Refining (B.C.) Ltd.

Parkland is growing. Our organization is powered by effective leadership, progressive strategies and industry-leading best practices — but more importantly, it is driven by talented, customer-focused people who value integrity, innovation and quality. We are looking for good-natured, hard-working candidates who want to build a rewarding career in a dynamic and collaborative work environment. We are a family and our family continues to grow.


Parkland Fuel Corporation acquired Chevron Canada’s downstream fuel business on October 1, 2017, this acquisition includes the Burnaby Refinery which is a modern 55,000 Barrel per day refinery located on Burrard Inlet near Vancouver, British Columbia. Our facility supplies a significant portion of southwestern BC’s gasoline, diesel, and jet fuel and is an important part of Parkland’s network of fuel and petroleum products facilities.

Overview of Position:

As a member of the refinery’s Projects Team, the Project Cost Control Analyst plays a critical role in ensuring:

The refinery’s portfolio of projects is executed predictably and efficiently, as shown through annual project lookbacks and benchmarking;
The Capital and Expense plans and forecasts are frequently monitored and accurate throughout the year;
The Projects Review Board (local portfolio Governance) and Parkland’s leadership team have the information required to make appropriate portfolio management decisions, such as stopping and starting projects and reassigning resources and capital;
Projects Project Managers have the required information to deliver projects within the approved parameters of scope, cost and schedule;
Key Responsibilities:

Supporting the Projects team in applying a consistent Project Controls (PC) work process:
Maintaining and streamlining the Cost Control (CC) work process used in Burnaby and training Project Managers PMs and Contractor Superintendents in the local cost control system (process, procedures and applications) and reporting expectations;
Coordinating and facilitating Estimate Assurance (EA) reviews on cost estimates for capital projects >$1MM Total Installed Cost (TIC);
Reviewing all projects Approval for Expenditure (AFE) forms for completeness and to verify the assessment of various determinations such as budget allocations and capitalisation rules;
Facilitating monthly Cost Control health check with PMs on projects >$1MM, to ensure CC deliverables and expectations are managed;
Support PMs in maintaining the Project Management database (Projects Highway) as primary source for CC data and information;
Monthly tracing of service order activity and status (no activity over the last 90 days or date past expected completion date) ensures accuracy of committed amounts and appropriate fund allocation;
Providing input into the development of the CC system to include procurement and contractor performance metrics (i.e. initial estimate, changes, final cost, challenges) and using the information to drive accountability and improvement;
Working in an integrated fashion with other members of the Project Controls team, and also supporting, Schedule Control, Change Control, Quantity Surveying, Progress and Performance Measurement, and Risk Management;
Working as a cost control integrator between Engineering teams (EP/EPCM), construction contractors, field engineering, contracts administration and procurement;
Facilitating a review and validation of Burnaby “All in one” labour rates annually.
Supporting the month end process for Capital and Expense reporting to Parkland Fuel Corp. and to the local refinery management:
Ensuring the projected cash flow is accurate through year-end and identifies and reviews variances. This role also manages and prepares year end accruals reports for forwarding to Financial Accounting;
Leading the monthly Project Review Board (PRB) meetings by preparing and presenting portfolio level summaries and forecasts to the refinery leadership team:
Support Projects Team Lead in preparing for Project Review Board (PRB) meetings. Prepares and presents portfolio level summaries and forecasts to the refinery leadership team;
Record and communicate decisions related to portfolio rebalancing based on current business focus, cash flow and resource availability;
Assessing the performance of the project portfolio at least annually, including its competitiveness through benchmarking using the Construction Industry Institute (CII) and by performing lookbacks on individual projects.


Qualifications and Skills:

3 -5 years-experience as a Cost Control Analysts within a production, manufacturing facility, construction contractor or an engineering (EP/EPC/EPCM) firm. Experience in an analytical or technical role within a refinery will also be considered. Prior experience related to Refining, Petro-chemical, or Construction industry is preferred;
Bachelor’s degree in Business or Finance, a Technical Diploma (BCIT or equivalent), and or Certification in Project Management;
Advanced skill level in MS Excel/Word and knowledge of MS Access or another database software. Knowledge of Primavera P6 scheduling software would be considered an asset in support of the PC Scheduler’s role;
JD Edwards and SAP knowledge is desirable;
Familiarity with Progress and Performance Management and Change Management Processes would be considered an asset.
Our main priority at Parkland is our people. As an employee, you can expect a fair workplace, a professional work environment, competitive compensation, outstanding benefits, and a share in our success through the Employee Share Purchase Plan and our Annual Incentive Plan.


Candidates must be legally able to work in Canada at this time. Parkland regrets that it is unable to sponsor employment Visas or consider individuals on time-limited Visa status for this position.

Our preferred method of application is online at www.parkland.ca


We thank all candidates in advance for their interest, however only those being considered will be contacted.


Parkland Fuel Corporation is committed to the principles of Employment Equity.

We strive to provide accessibility in employment to ensure equal access to employment opportunities for candidates, including persons with disabilities. Parkland Fuel Corporation will endeavor to provide accommodation to persons with disabilities in the recruitment process upon request. If you are selected for an interview and you require accommodation due to a disability, please notify us upon scheduling your interview.

