The successful incumbent will have:
University Degree in a Business or Science program
Must have at least 2 years working experience within forecasting/analytical roles, with preference given to those having worked in the pharmaceutical industry;
Advanced proficiency with MS Excel, including pivot tables, v-lookups and macros as well as with MS PowerPoint;
Strong and proven analytic and mathematic problem solving skills with exceptional attention to detail;
Experience working in cross-functional teams;
Agility to learn new software applications and technologies;
Demonstrated time management, problem solving and decision making competencies;
Proven effective presentation, analytical and customer relationship abilities;
Proven ability to comprehend, analyze and research problems of a complex nature, make decisions and/or present recommendations;
Demonstrated ability to prioritize, multi-task and maintain flexibility in a fast-paced environment;
Ability to work autonomously and in teams to effectively prioritize multiple projects and associated deliverables;
Excellent communication skills and comfortable interacting with customers backed by solid spoken and written English;
Developed communication skills and the ability to work in a collaborative team environment;
Preference for fast paced, rapid start-up culture demonstrating the values of results, teamwork, energy, agility, respect, and can-do environment.

